00:29:38.480 --> 00:29:41.840
"Rockbuds crunched like
skulls beneath Dalinar's boots

00:29:41.840 --> 00:29:44.310
as he charged across
the burning field.

00:29:44.310 --> 00:29:47.900
His elites tromped behind him,
a hand-picked force of soldiers

00:29:47.900 --> 00:29:49.910
both light-eyed and dark.

00:29:49.910 --> 00:29:51.510
They weren't an honor guard.

00:29:51.510 --> 00:29:54.110
Dalinar didn't need guards.

00:29:54.110 --> 00:29:56.180
These were simply the men
he considered competent

00:29:56.180 --> 00:29:58.670
enough not to embarrass him.

00:29:58.670 --> 00:30:01.030
"Around him, rockbuds smoldered.

00:30:01.030 --> 00:30:03.810
Moss, dried from the
summer heat and long days

00:30:03.810 --> 00:30:05.600
between storms
this time of year,

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:08.170
flared up in waves,
setting the rockbud shells

00:30:08.170 --> 00:30:10.120
themselves aflame.

00:30:10.120 --> 00:30:13.670
Dalinar charged the smoke,
trusting in his padded armor

00:30:13.670 --> 00:30:15.550
and thick boots to protect him.

00:30:15.550 --> 00:30:18.240
Flamespren, like tiny
people made of fire,

00:30:18.240 --> 00:30:21.760
danced from one patch
of flame to the next.

00:30:21.760 --> 00:30:24.710
"The enemy, pressed by
his armies from the North,

00:30:24.710 --> 00:30:27.710
had pulled back into
the town just ahead.

00:30:27.710 --> 00:30:30.190
Dalinar had held himself
back with difficulty

00:30:30.190 --> 00:30:32.087
from entering that
initial clash.

00:30:32.087 --> 00:30:34.170
He'd known the real fighting
would take place here

00:30:34.170 --> 00:30:35.790
in the town.

00:30:35.790 --> 00:30:40.170
He hadn't expected the enemy
to, in a desperate move, fire

00:30:40.170 --> 00:30:42.170
this plain, burning
their own crops

00:30:42.170 --> 00:30:44.150
to block the southern approach.

00:30:44.150 --> 00:30:45.430
"Well, no matter.

00:30:45.430 --> 00:30:48.560
The fires could go to damnation
for all Dalinar cared.

00:30:48.560 --> 00:30:50.140
He led his men in a charge.

00:30:50.140 --> 00:30:52.600
And though some were overwhelmed
by the smoke or heat,

00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:54.620
most stayed with him.

00:30:54.620 --> 00:30:56.820
They'd crash into the
enemy from the South,

00:30:56.820 --> 00:31:00.410
pressing them between his
men here and the main army.

00:31:00.410 --> 00:31:03.540
Hammer and anvil, the
best kind of tactic,

00:31:03.540 --> 00:31:08.180
the type that didn't allow his
enemies to get away from him.

00:31:08.180 --> 00:31:10.280
"As Dalinar burst
from the smoky air,

00:31:10.280 --> 00:31:13.190
he found a few lines of
spearmen hastily making ranks

00:31:13.190 --> 00:31:15.300
on the southern
edge of the town.

00:31:15.300 --> 00:31:16.960
There were remnants of a wall.

00:31:16.960 --> 00:31:19.300
But that had been
torn down years ago.

00:31:19.300 --> 00:31:21.560
Dalinar had forgotten
the town's name.

00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:23.490
But the location was ideal.

00:31:23.490 --> 00:31:26.630
A large ridge to the East made
a natural break from the storms

00:31:26.630 --> 00:31:31.830
and had allowed this place to
sprawl almost like a real city.

00:31:31.830 --> 00:31:33.950
"Dalinar screamed at
the enemy soldiers,

00:31:33.950 --> 00:31:38.310
beating a sword-- just a regular
longsword-- against his shield.

00:31:38.310 --> 00:31:40.410
He wore a sturdy
breastplate and helm along

00:31:40.410 --> 00:31:42.070
with iron-lined boots.

00:31:42.070 --> 00:31:43.820
The spearmen ahead
of him wavered

00:31:43.820 --> 00:31:46.270
as his elites roared
from the smoke and flame,

00:31:46.270 --> 00:31:49.000
shouting a
bloodthirsty cacaphony.

00:31:49.000 --> 00:31:51.780
A few of the spearmen
dropped weapons and ran.

00:31:51.780 --> 00:31:54.410
Fearspren, like
globs of violet goo,

00:31:54.410 --> 00:31:57.790
wriggled up from the ground en
masse around the enemy rank.

00:31:57.790 --> 00:31:59.240
"Dalinar grinned.

00:31:59.240 --> 00:32:02.030
He didn't need
Shards to intimidate.

00:32:02.030 --> 00:32:05.300
He hit the spearman
like a boulder,

00:32:05.300 --> 00:32:08.290
rolling through a grove of
saplings, swinging his sword

00:32:08.290 --> 00:32:10.750
and sending limbs into the air.

00:32:10.750 --> 00:32:12.880
A good fight was about momentum.

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:13.570
Don't stop.

00:32:13.570 --> 00:32:14.630
Don't think.

00:32:14.630 --> 00:32:16.620
Drive forward and
convince your enemies

00:32:16.620 --> 00:32:19.830
that they were as
good as dead already.

00:32:19.830 --> 00:32:22.290
That way, they'd fight
you less as you sent them

00:32:22.290 --> 00:32:24.190
to their pyres.

00:32:24.190 --> 00:32:26.210
As he waded among
them, the spearmen

00:32:26.210 --> 00:32:28.550
thrust weapons
frantically toward him,

00:32:28.550 --> 00:32:30.410
less trying to killed
Dalinar and more

00:32:30.410 --> 00:32:33.110
trying to push away this madman.

00:32:33.110 --> 00:32:34.440
Their ranks collapsed.

00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:38.500
And many of them turned their
sides to Dalinar's elites.

00:32:38.500 --> 00:32:42.340
"Dalinar laughed, slamming aside
a pair of spears with a shield,

00:32:42.340 --> 00:32:45.400
then disemboweling one man
with a sword deep in the gut.

00:32:45.400 --> 00:32:49.110
He jumped and left the man to
drop his spear, and in a panic,

00:32:49.110 --> 00:32:51.186
trying to grab at his entrails.

00:32:51.186 --> 00:32:53.310
The man's allies backed
away at the horrific sight.

00:32:53.310 --> 00:32:56.660
So Dalinar came in swinging,
catching the two off balance,

00:32:56.660 --> 00:33:00.160
killing them with the sword
that bore their friend's blood.

00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:03.500
"Dalinar's elites decimated
the now broken line.

00:33:03.500 --> 00:33:06.057
Dalinar himself pushed forward,
keeping momentum, shearing

00:33:06.057 --> 00:33:07.890
through the ranks until
he reached the back,

00:33:07.890 --> 00:33:11.520
breathing deeply and wiping
ashen sweat from his face.

00:33:11.520 --> 00:33:13.330
A young spearman
fell before him,

00:33:13.330 --> 00:33:15.130
crying, screaming
for his mother as he

00:33:15.130 --> 00:33:18.280
crawled across the stony
ground, trailing blood.

00:33:18.280 --> 00:33:21.620
Fearspren mixed with
Painspren all around.

00:33:21.620 --> 00:33:24.070
"Dalinar shook his head,
picking up a fallen spear

00:33:24.070 --> 00:33:26.200
and striding past the
youth, slamming it down

00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:27.630
in the boy's back.

00:33:27.630 --> 00:33:29.850
Men often cried for their
parents as they died.

00:33:29.850 --> 00:33:31.440
Didn't matter how old they were.

00:33:31.440 --> 00:33:34.730
He'd seen gray beards do it,
same as kids like this one.

00:33:34.730 --> 00:33:37.450
'He's not much younger than
I am,' Dalinar thought.

00:33:37.450 --> 00:33:41.370
'Maybe 17.' But then Dalinar
had never felt young,

00:33:41.370 --> 00:33:43.390
regardless of his age.

00:33:43.390 --> 00:33:45.080
His elites filled in
behind him, having

00:33:45.080 --> 00:33:47.050
carved the enemy line in two.

00:33:47.050 --> 00:33:49.590
Dalinar danced, shaking
off his bloody blade,

00:33:49.590 --> 00:33:52.890
feeling alert, excited,
but not yet alive.

00:33:52.890 --> 00:33:54.180
Where was it?

00:33:54.180 --> 00:33:56.180
'Come on,' he thought.

00:33:56.180 --> 00:33:57.970
"A larger group of
soldiers hiked down

00:33:57.970 --> 00:34:01.670
the street toward him, led by
some officers in white and red.

00:34:01.670 --> 00:34:03.600
Dalinar could see from
the way they pulled up,

00:34:03.600 --> 00:34:05.900
alarmed, that they hadn't
expected their spearmen

00:34:05.900 --> 00:34:07.760
to fall so quickly.

00:34:07.760 --> 00:34:09.210
Dalinar charged.

00:34:09.210 --> 00:34:10.330
His elites knew to watch.

00:34:10.330 --> 00:34:13.050
So he was followed by
a force of 50 or 60.

00:34:13.050 --> 00:34:16.010
The rest had to finish off
the unfortunate spearmen.

00:34:16.010 --> 00:34:17.449
Well, 50 would do.

00:34:17.449 --> 00:34:19.280
The crowded confines
of the town would mean

00:34:19.280 --> 00:34:21.670
Dalinar shouldn't need more.

00:34:21.670 --> 00:34:24.420
As he neared this newer force,
he focused his attention

00:34:24.420 --> 00:34:27.000
on the one man riding a horse.

00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:28.699
The fellow wore
plate armor obviously

00:34:28.699 --> 00:34:31.340
meant to recreate Shardplate,
though it was only

00:34:31.340 --> 00:34:32.830
of common steel.

00:34:32.830 --> 00:34:36.120
It lacked the beauty,
the power, of true Plate.

00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:39.090
He still looked like he was the
most important person around.

00:34:39.090 --> 00:34:41.226
Hopefully, that would
mean he was the best.

00:34:41.226 --> 00:34:43.380
"The man's honor guard
rushed to engage.

00:34:43.380 --> 00:34:45.909
And Dalinar felt something
stir inside of him

00:34:45.909 --> 00:34:48.350
like a thirst, a physical need.

00:34:48.350 --> 00:34:52.250
Challenge, he needed
a challenge, storm it!

00:34:52.250 --> 00:34:54.610
He let his elites
handle the honor guard.

00:34:54.610 --> 00:34:56.949
He made his way
toward the Brightlord.

00:34:56.949 --> 00:34:59.470
The man wasn't old enough
to be the highprince.

00:34:59.470 --> 00:35:01.780
Some other important lighteyes?

00:35:01.780 --> 00:35:04.550
Or didn't Dalinar remember
something about a son

00:35:04.550 --> 00:35:07.000
during Gavilar's endless
planning meetings?

00:35:07.000 --> 00:35:09.570
Well, this man certainly looked
grand on that white mare,

00:35:09.570 --> 00:35:12.400
watching the battle
behind a helmed face.

00:35:12.400 --> 00:35:15.230
"The foe turned toward
Dalinar and raised his sword

00:35:15.230 --> 00:35:18.490
to his helm in a sign
of a challenge accepted.

00:35:18.490 --> 00:35:20.720
Idiot.

00:35:20.720 --> 00:35:22.500
Dalinar raised his
shield arm and pointed,

00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:24.166
counting on at least
one of his strikers

00:35:24.166 --> 00:35:25.760
to have lived and
stayed with him.

00:35:25.760 --> 00:35:27.750
Indeed, Jenin
stepped up, unhooked

00:35:27.750 --> 00:35:29.120
the short bow from his back.

00:35:29.120 --> 00:35:31.460
And as the Brightlord
shouted in surprise,

00:35:31.460 --> 00:35:34.080
shot the horse in the chest.

00:35:34.080 --> 00:35:36.170
"'Hate shooting
horses,' Jenin grumbled,

00:35:36.170 --> 00:35:37.760
as the beast reared in pain.

00:35:37.760 --> 00:35:41.580
"like throwing 1,000 broams into
the storming ocean, Brightlord.

00:35:41.580 --> 00:35:43.630
"'I'll buy you two
when we finish this,"

00:35:43.630 --> 00:35:47.740
Dalinar said as the Brightlord
tumbled backward off his horse.

00:35:47.740 --> 00:35:50.430
"Dalinar dodged around flashing
hooves and snorts of pain,

00:35:50.430 --> 00:35:52.170
seeking out the fallen man.

00:35:52.170 --> 00:35:55.150
He was pleased to
find the enemy rising.

00:35:55.150 --> 00:35:56.890
Dalinar came in swinging.

00:35:56.890 --> 00:35:58.880
The Brightlord managed
to get his sword up.

00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:01.610
And Dalinar battered it away
and then dropped his own shield

00:36:01.610 --> 00:36:04.210
completely, and came in with
a two-handed power swing,

00:36:04.210 --> 00:36:07.250
intending to knock the
lighteyed soldier back down.

00:36:07.250 --> 00:36:09.760
Fortunately, the man was good
enough to recover his stance

00:36:09.760 --> 00:36:12.450
and intercept the
blow with his shield.

00:36:12.450 --> 00:36:14.410
They probably heard
the subsequent crack

00:36:14.410 --> 00:36:15.980
all the way in Kholinar.

00:36:15.980 --> 00:36:19.510
indeed, it vibrated
up Dalinar's arms.

00:36:19.510 --> 00:36:22.500
"Momentum, life
was about momentum.

00:36:22.500 --> 00:36:25.360
Pick a direction and don't
let anything, man or storm,

00:36:25.360 --> 00:36:26.850
turn you aside.

00:36:26.850 --> 00:36:28.450
Dalinar battered
at the Brightlord,

00:36:28.450 --> 00:36:31.830
driving him backward until
surprisingly, the men managed

00:36:31.830 --> 00:36:33.850
to pull a feint,
and getting close,

00:36:33.850 --> 00:36:36.030
to ram Dalinar with his shield.

00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:38.220
Dalinar ducked the sword
swing that followed.

00:36:38.220 --> 00:36:41.310
But the backhand hit him
solidly on the side of the head,

00:36:41.310 --> 00:36:43.670
sending him stumbling,
his helm twisted,

00:36:43.670 --> 00:36:47.030
metal bent by the blow biting
into his scalp, drawing blood.

00:36:47.030 --> 00:36:47.810
He saw double.

00:36:47.810 --> 00:36:49.730
His vision swimming.

00:36:49.730 --> 00:36:53.000
"He roared at the lord, as
the lord smartly came in

00:36:53.000 --> 00:36:54.260
for the kill.

00:36:54.260 --> 00:36:57.340
Dalinar swept his blade up in
a lurching, full-shoulder blow,

00:36:57.340 --> 00:36:59.140
slapping the lord's
weapon out of his hands

00:36:59.140 --> 00:37:01.330
and tossing both swords away.

00:37:01.330 --> 00:37:04.910
The man in turn punched Dalinar
in the face with his gauntlet.

00:37:04.910 --> 00:37:07.690
And Dalinar's nose crunched.

00:37:07.690 --> 00:37:10.120
Dalinar fell to his
knees, vision blurry.

00:37:10.120 --> 00:37:12.620
His foe was breathing deeply,
cursing between breaths,

00:37:12.620 --> 00:37:15.310
winded by the short,
frantic contest.

00:37:15.310 --> 00:37:19.400
The Brightlord fished
at his belt for a knife.

00:37:19.400 --> 00:37:22.760
"An emotion stirred
instead of Dalinar, a fire

00:37:22.760 --> 00:37:25.030
that filled the pit within.

00:37:25.030 --> 00:37:27.760
It washed through him and
awakened him, bringing clarity.

00:37:27.760 --> 00:37:30.220
The sounds of his elites
fighting the Brightlord's honor

00:37:30.220 --> 00:37:33.670
guard faded, metal on metal
becoming distant clinks, grunts

00:37:33.670 --> 00:37:35.370
becoming like a humming.

00:37:35.370 --> 00:37:36.760
Dalinar grinned.

00:37:36.760 --> 00:37:39.000
Then that grin became
a toothy smile.

00:37:39.000 --> 00:37:41.550
His vision returned
as the Brightlord, who

00:37:41.550 --> 00:37:44.130
had just retrieved his
knife, looked up and started,

00:37:44.130 --> 00:37:45.550
stumbling back.

00:37:45.550 --> 00:37:47.530
He seemed horrified.

00:37:47.530 --> 00:37:50.400
"Dalinar roared, spitting
blood and throwing himself

00:37:50.400 --> 00:37:51.370
at the enemy.

00:37:51.370 --> 00:37:53.470
The swing that came
for him seem pitiful.

00:37:53.470 --> 00:37:56.190
And Dalinar ducked it, pushing
his shoulder against his foe

00:37:56.190 --> 00:37:57.630
and shoving him backward.

00:37:57.630 --> 00:37:59.650
Something thrummed
inside of Dalinar,

00:37:59.650 --> 00:38:03.130
the pulse of the battle, the
rhythm of killing and dying,

00:38:03.130 --> 00:38:05.220
the Thrill.

00:38:05.220 --> 00:38:07.960
He knocked his opponent
off balance, then reached

00:38:07.960 --> 00:38:09.110
for his sword.

00:38:09.110 --> 00:38:12.330
"Dym, however, hollered his
name and tossed him a pole axe,

00:38:12.330 --> 00:38:15.730
with a hook on one side and
broad, thin axe on the other.

00:38:15.730 --> 00:38:17.910
Dalinar seized it
from the air and spun,

00:38:17.910 --> 00:38:19.412
ducking the lord's swing.

00:38:19.412 --> 00:38:20.870
At the same time,
he hooked the man

00:38:20.870 --> 00:38:23.720
around the ankle with
the axe-head and yanked.

00:38:23.720 --> 00:38:27.000
The Brightlord fell
in a clatter of steel.

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:29.250
"Unfortunately, before
Dalinar could attack further,

00:38:29.250 --> 00:38:31.410
the honor guard became a bother.

00:38:31.410 --> 00:38:34.280
Two had managed to extricate
themselves from Dalinar's men.

00:38:34.280 --> 00:38:36.860
And they came to the
defense of their lord.

00:38:36.860 --> 00:38:39.140
Dalinar caught their sword
strikes on his polearm

00:38:39.140 --> 00:38:41.170
and twisted about,
backing away and bringing

00:38:41.170 --> 00:38:44.030
the axe-head slamming
into one man's side.

00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:46.390
Dalinar ripped it
free and spun again,

00:38:46.390 --> 00:38:48.900
this time smashing the weapon
against the rising lord's head

00:38:48.900 --> 00:38:51.600
and sending him to his knees.

00:38:51.600 --> 00:38:53.340
"Then he came back
and barely managed

00:38:53.340 --> 00:38:56.410
to catch the other guard's sword
on the haft of his polearm.

00:38:56.410 --> 00:38:59.150
Dalinar pushed upward, holding
the polearm in two hands,

00:38:59.150 --> 00:39:01.394
sweeping the guard's blade
into the air over his head

00:39:01.394 --> 00:39:03.310
and stepping forward
until he was face-to-face

00:39:03.310 --> 00:39:04.210
with the fellow.

00:39:04.210 --> 00:39:07.420
He could feel the man's
breath on his face.

00:39:07.420 --> 00:39:09.680
"Dalinar spit blood
from a shattered nose

00:39:09.680 --> 00:39:12.470
into the guard's eyes, then
kicked him in the stomach.

00:39:12.470 --> 00:39:14.990
He turned toward the lord,
who had scrambled again

00:39:14.990 --> 00:39:17.480
to his feet, and was
now trying to flee.

00:39:17.480 --> 00:39:19.660
Dalinar growled,
full of the Thrill,

00:39:19.660 --> 00:39:21.420
and swung his
polearm by one hand,

00:39:21.420 --> 00:39:22.960
hooking the spike
in the lord's side

00:39:22.960 --> 00:39:25.780
and yanking, dropping
him a third time.

00:39:25.780 --> 00:39:26.510
The lord rolled.

00:39:26.510 --> 00:39:29.620
And this time, he was greeted
by the sight of Dalinar slamming

00:39:29.620 --> 00:39:31.730
his polearm down by
two hands, driving

00:39:31.730 --> 00:39:35.100
the spike right through the
breastplate and into the chest.

00:39:35.100 --> 00:39:36.860
It made a satisfying crunch.

00:39:36.860 --> 00:39:39.840
And Dalinar pulled
it out, bloodied.

00:39:39.840 --> 00:39:42.007
"The blow seemed
a signal of sorts.

00:39:42.007 --> 00:39:43.590
And the honor guard
and other soldiers

00:39:43.590 --> 00:39:45.590
finally broke before his elites.

00:39:45.590 --> 00:39:47.180
Dalinar grinned
as he watched them

00:39:47.180 --> 00:39:49.270
go, Gloryspren
popping up around him

00:39:49.270 --> 00:39:51.560
like glowing, golden spheres.

00:39:51.560 --> 00:39:53.270
His men took out
their short bows

00:39:53.270 --> 00:39:55.630
and managed to drop a good
dozen of the fleeing enemy

00:39:55.630 --> 00:39:56.970
in the backs.

00:39:56.970 --> 00:40:01.150
Damnation, it felt good to best
to force larger than his own.

00:40:01.150 --> 00:40:02.810
"The Thrill dwindled.

00:40:02.810 --> 00:40:05.890
He could never seem to hold
onto it as long as he wanted.

00:40:05.890 --> 00:40:10.220
Nearby, the man he'd
felled groaned softly.

00:40:10.220 --> 00:40:14.180
Dalinar stepped over, curious,
kicking at the armored chest.

00:40:14.180 --> 00:40:17.000
"Why, the man said
from within his helm.

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:18.780
'Why us?'

00:40:18.780 --> 00:40:21.780
"'Don't know,' Dalinar said,
tossing the polearm back

00:40:21.780 --> 00:40:22.920
to Dym.

00:40:22.920 --> 00:40:25.530
"'You-- you don't know?'

00:40:25.530 --> 00:40:26.860
"'My brother chooses.

00:40:26.860 --> 00:40:29.000
I just go where he points me.

00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:30.457
"He gestured toward
the dying man.

00:40:30.457 --> 00:40:32.790
And Dym rammed his sword in
the hole in the breastplate,

00:40:32.790 --> 00:40:34.080
finishing the job.

00:40:34.080 --> 00:40:35.810
The fellow had fought
reasonably well.

00:40:35.810 --> 00:40:38.190
No need to extend his suffering.

00:40:38.190 --> 00:40:41.240
"Another soldier approached,
handing Dalinar his sword.

00:40:41.240 --> 00:40:44.180
It had a chip the size of
a thumb right in the blade.

00:40:44.180 --> 00:40:46.670
Looked like it
had bent, as well.

00:40:46.670 --> 00:40:48.910
"'You're supposed to stick
it in the squishy parts,

00:40:48.910 --> 00:40:52.880
Brightlord,' Dym said, 'not
pound it against the hard

00:40:52.880 --> 00:40:54.110
parts.'

00:40:54.110 --> 00:40:56.570
"'I'll keep that in
mind,' Dalinar said,

00:40:56.570 --> 00:40:58.820
tossing the sword aside,
as one of his men selected

00:40:58.820 --> 00:41:01.610
a replacement from among the
fallen of high enough rank

00:41:01.610 --> 00:41:02.920
to have one.

00:41:02.920 --> 00:41:05.820
"'You all right, Brightlord?'

00:41:05.820 --> 00:41:07.830
"'Never been better,'
Dalinar said,

00:41:07.830 --> 00:41:10.200
then sucked the blood up
through his broken nose.

00:41:10.200 --> 00:41:12.510
Hurt like damnation itself.

00:41:12.510 --> 00:41:14.100
"His men formed around him.

00:41:14.100 --> 00:41:16.744
And Dalinar led the way
further down the street.

00:41:16.744 --> 00:41:18.160
Before too long,
he could make out

00:41:18.160 --> 00:41:20.690
the bulk of the enemy still
fighting ahead, harried

00:41:20.690 --> 00:41:22.490
by his main army.

00:41:22.490 --> 00:41:25.040
He halted his elites,
contemplating.

00:41:25.040 --> 00:41:28.690
"'Orders, sir?' Thakka,
Captain of the Elites, asked.

00:41:28.690 --> 00:41:30.710
"'Raid those buildings,'
Dalinar said,

00:41:30.710 --> 00:41:32.120
pointing at a line of homes.

00:41:32.120 --> 00:41:34.800
'Let's see how well they fight
while they see us rounding up

00:41:34.800 --> 00:41:36.780
their families.'

00:41:36.780 --> 00:41:39.040
"Thakka nodded,
shouting the orders.

00:41:39.040 --> 00:41:40.770
Dalinar reached for some water.

00:41:40.770 --> 00:41:42.440
He'd need to meet
up with Sadeas,

00:41:42.440 --> 00:41:45.760
and-- something slammed
into Dalinar's shoulder.

00:41:45.760 --> 00:41:48.200
He got only a brief
sight of it, a black blur

00:41:48.200 --> 00:41:50.250
that hit with the force
of a roundhouse kick.

00:41:50.250 --> 00:41:51.070
It threw him down.

00:41:51.070 --> 00:41:53.490
And pain flared
up from his side.

00:41:53.490 --> 00:41:56.630
"'An arrow?' he said, blinking
as he found himself lying

00:41:56.630 --> 00:41:57.470
on the ground.

00:41:57.470 --> 00:42:01.000
A storming arrow sprouted
from his right shoulder, one

00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:02.640
with a long, thick shaft.

00:42:02.640 --> 00:42:05.380
It had gone right
through the plate.

00:42:05.380 --> 00:42:07.430
"'My Lord,' Thakka
said, kneeling,

00:42:07.430 --> 00:42:08.990
shielding Dalinar with his body.

00:42:08.990 --> 00:42:09.490
Kelek!

00:42:09.490 --> 00:42:10.700
Brightlord, are you--

00:42:10.700 --> 00:42:14.260
"'Who in damnation shot
that?' Dalinar demanded.

00:42:14.260 --> 00:42:17.770
"'Up there,' Dym said,
pointing at a ridge above town.

00:42:17.770 --> 00:42:21.330
"'That's got to be over
300 yards,' Dalinar said,

00:42:21.330 --> 00:42:23.410
shoving Thakka
aside and standing.

00:42:23.410 --> 00:42:25.470
'That can't possibly--

00:42:25.470 --> 00:42:26.390
"He was watching.

00:42:26.390 --> 00:42:28.770
So he was able to jump out
of the way of the next arrow,

00:42:28.770 --> 00:42:31.560
which dropped a mere foot from
him, slamming against the stone

00:42:31.560 --> 00:42:32.670
ground.

00:42:32.670 --> 00:42:35.200
Dalinar stared at it,
then started shouting.

00:42:35.200 --> 00:42:35.950
"'Horses!

00:42:35.950 --> 00:42:37.640
Where are the storming horses?'

00:42:37.640 --> 00:42:39.390
"Had the fires delayed them?

00:42:39.390 --> 00:42:40.680
No, fortunately.

00:42:40.680 --> 00:42:43.260
A small group of soldiers had
guided them more carefully

00:42:43.260 --> 00:42:45.717
across the fields, but
had caught up by now.

00:42:45.717 --> 00:42:47.550
They stood with the
rear guard of the elites

00:42:47.550 --> 00:42:50.070
and came trotting forward as
Dalinar's order was passed,

00:42:50.070 --> 00:42:52.110
bringing all 11 horses.

00:42:52.110 --> 00:42:53.920
Dalinar had to
dodge another arrow

00:42:53.920 --> 00:42:56.490
as he seized the reins of
Fullnight, his black gelding,

00:42:56.490 --> 00:42:58.560
and heaved himself
into the saddle.

00:42:58.560 --> 00:43:00.190
He galloped back the
way he'd came in,

00:43:00.190 --> 00:43:02.390
trailed by 10 of his best men.

00:43:02.390 --> 00:43:05.650
There had to be a
way up that slope.

00:43:05.650 --> 00:43:07.950
There, a rocky set
of switchbacks,

00:43:07.950 --> 00:43:10.649
shallow enough that he didn't
mind running Fullnight up them.

